    "Implementation Details.",
    "We compare SSH against AFLoRA and LaMDA under consistent experimental conditions.",
    "For AFLoRA and LaMDA, we set the rank r = 32, while for SSH, we select n = 5000 Hartley spectrum points.",
    "The models are trained using a learning rate of 2 × 10 -4, with a batch size of 32 for XSUM and 64 for CNN/DailyMail.",
    "Training is conducted for 25 epochs on XSUM and 15 epochs on CNN/DailyMail."
